# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HRIV Trivy ignore list
#
# Trivy consumes this file (via `trivyignores:` on the aquasecurity/trivy-action
# step in .github/workflows/ci.yaml) and suppresses the listed CVEs from both
# the PR-time table scan and the main/tag SARIF upload. Entries here are
# *explicit, documented, reviewed decisions* — each group below has a
# justification comment and is dated for review.
#
# Review cadence: quarterly. Last reviewed: 2026-04-20.
#
# Adding an entry requires:
#   1) A justification comment referencing *why* the CVE is non-reachable, not
#      fixable, or an accepted residual risk in HRIV's specific deployment.
#   2) A group header so the entry is discoverable when reading the file top
#      to bottom — don't just append a bare CVE-ID at the bottom.
#   3) The CVE's severity as a trailing `# sev=...` comment so at-a-glance
#      review surfaces the ones that are critical/high.
#
# Removing an entry is *free* — the next Trivy scan will re-report the CVE.
# Prefer removing an entry whenever the justification no longer holds (e.g.
# if HRIV starts shipping a codec delegate that was previously disabled in
# backend/Dockerfile, the matching ignore block must go).
#
# NOTE: the backend image deliberately does NOT install `libvips42t64` from
# Debian — it builds `libvips` from source with unused codec delegates
# compiled out (see `libvips-build` stage in backend/Dockerfile).  The RAW /
# HEIF / JPEG-XL / OpenEXR / ImageMagick / MATLAB / Poppler / GnuPG CVE
# groups that used to dominate this file are *physically absent* from the
# runtime image and no longer need ignore entries.
#
# Format reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------


# --- backend/libarchive13t64: archive-format parser CVEs ---------------------
# libvips is compiled against libarchive to support the `dzsave` tile writer
# (directory output of .dzi + _files tree is libarchive-free, but the module
# is linked regardless).  HRIV only writes DZI output; it never *reads* a
# user-supplied archive (no .zip/.tar/.rar/.iso paths reach libvips). The
# RAR5, RAR, and ISO9660 decoder CVEs below are therefore non-reachable —
# the parsers exist in the library image but nothing in HRIV's pipeline
# dispatches to them. Debian has not yet shipped a fix in trixie-security.
#
# Packages: libarchive13t64
CVE-2026-4111   # sev=high (RAR5 infinite-loop DoS)
CVE-2026-4424   # sev=high (RAR information disclosure)
CVE-2026-5121   # sev=high (ISO9660 integer overflow)

# --- util-linux chfn/chsh info leak ------------------------------------------
# CVE-2022-0563 (and the sibling chsh/login entries) require an interactive
# `chfn`/`chsh`/`login` session. HRIV container images do not run an
# interactive shell — the entrypoint is uvicorn (backend), nginx (frontend),
# or python -m app.backup (backup). No attacker can trigger an interactive
# readline session inside the container. Debian has declared these
# unreachable in container contexts and does not intend to fix.
#
# Packages: util-linux, bsdutils, mount, login, libblkid1, libmount1,
#           libsmartcols1, libuuid1, libfdisk1
CVE-2007-5686   # sev=low
CVE-2022-0563   # sev=low
CVE-2024-56433  # sev=low
CVE-2025-14104  # sev=low
CVE-2026-27456  # sev=medium
CVE-2026-3184   # sev=low

# --- backup/zlib1g: minizip Zip64-header heap overflow -----------------------
# HRIV backup service runs only `pg_dump` and `psql`; minizip is a zlib
# function for ZIP-archive handling that the backup workflow never invokes.
# Fix is in Debian unstable (sid) but not yet backported to trixie/bookworm
# as of this writing.
CVE-2023-45853  # sev=critical  (scope: backup/zlib1g)

# --- backup/libsqlite3-0: SQLite parser integer overflow ---------------------
# HRIV backup service opens no user-provided SQLite databases. libsqlite3-0
# is pulled in as a dependency of `libpython3.13-stdlib` (for `import sqlite3`
# availability). The backup worker does not `import sqlite3`; ripgrep
# confirms zero references. No attacker-controlled input reaches the parser.
CVE-2025-7458   # sev=critical  (scope: backup/libsqlite3-0)
